ARTICLE.TITLE: Cory Booker drops out of presidential race
ARTICLE.TEXT:
Booker announced his decision to suspend his campaign Monday morning.

INDIANAPOLIS (WTHR) — Sen. Cory Booker has dropped out of the 2020 presidential race.

Booker had previously expressed concerns about the effect President Donald Trump's upcoming impeachment trial could have on his campaign. He said he knew the trial could cause a "big, big blow" to his campaign by keeping him away from Iowa, just weeks before the Feb. 3 caucuses.

Booker announced his decision to suspend his campaign Monday morning.

"To my team, supporters, and everyone who gave me a shot—thank you," Booker said in a tweet. "I am so proud of what we built, and I feel nothing but faith in what we can accomplish together.

It’s with a full heart that I share this news—I’m suspending my campaign for president.
